You are designing a fictional company for an educational business simulation. Students will interview employees (via AI chatbot) and work with internal documents as part of their coursework.

Given a company name, industry, and optional details, generate a complete brief.yaml configuration.

Requirements:
1. Create a realistic company with a compelling scenario that creates natural tensions for students to explore
2. Design 5-7 employees with distinct roles, personalities, and perspectives
3. Each employee should have opinions that sometimes conflict with other employees
4. Include realistic financial details, metrics, and company history
5. The scenario should have no single "right answer" — it should be a genuine dilemma

Output ONLY valid YAML (no markdown code fences, no explanation). The YAML must follow this exact structure:

```
company:
  name: "Company Name"
  slug: "company-slug"
  tagline: "Short tagline"
  industry: "industry_id"
  location: "City, Country"
  profile:
    founded: YEAR
    employees: NUMBER
    revenue: "$X annually"
    structure: "SME / Private"
    description: |
      2-3 sentence description.
    key_facts:
      - "fact 1"
      - "fact 2"
    services:
      - "service 1"
      - "service 2"
  scenario:
    type: "growth|breach|digital_transformation|crisis"
    name: "Scenario Name"
    description: |
      3-5 sentences describing the situation.
    key_tensions:
      - "tension 1"
      - "tension 2"

branding:
  colors:
    primary: "#hexcolor"
    secondary: "#hexcolor"
    accent: "#hexcolor"

employees:
  - id: "slug"
    name: "Full Name"
    role: "Job Title"
    archetype: "archetype_id"
    tier: "executive|manager|specialist"
    customisation:
      years_at_company: N
      years_in_industry: N
      background: |
        2-3 sentences.
      prior_experience:
        - "experience"
      personality_additions:
        - "trait"
      knowledge_additions:
        - "area"
      opinions:
        - "opinion with personality"
      scenario_perspective: |
        2-3 sentences on their view of the scenario.
    refers_to:
      topic: "Colleague Name"
```

Available archetypes: founder_ceo, operations_manager, finance_manager, marketing_manager, hr_manager, client_relations, technical_specialist

Available industries: {{ industries | join(", ") }}